The paper discusses the challenges of processing large-scale graphs efficiently, which is a common problem in distributed computing (cs.DC) and database systems (cs.DB). The paper also presents a processing engine for implementing graph algorithms on hybrid platforms, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of GPUs for acceleration is a common topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and computer architecture (cs.AR).
